org.spongepowered.api.text.selector

Interface Selector


  • public interface Selector
    Represents an immutable selector of targets, as used in commands.

    In Vanilla, selectors are mostly represented as plain text, starting with an @ symbol and followed by a single character signifying the type, and finally the (optional) arguments in brackets.

    As an example, the all player selector is @a, and with a radius of 20 it would be @a[r=20].

    See Also:
    Target selectors on the Minecraft Wiki
